Text:
Please help, I cannot install biganalytics_1.1.3 in my windows 7 32-bit system

> library(biganalytics)

Error: package ‘biganalytics’ is not installed for 'arch = i386'
In addition: Warning message:
package ‘biganalytics’ was built under R version 3.1.1 

I even tried the following command in cmd prompt
> R CMD INSTALL --build biganalytics_1.1.3.tar.gz

It's showing error 
ERROR: configuration failed for package 'biganalytics'

Also with the option install.package
> install.packages("D:\\\\DataMining\\\\Rpackages\\\\biganalytics_1.1.3.zip",repos=NULL)

Installing package into ‘C:/Users/859673/Documents/R/win-library/3.1’
(as ‘lib’ is unspecified)
package ‘biganalytics’ successfully unpacked and MD5 sums checked

> library(biganalytics)

Error: package ‘biganalytics’ is not installed for 'arch = i386'
In addition: Warning message:
package ‘biganalytics’ was built under R version 3.1.1 

It is still showing the same error
